ious illuvitae) on a cr while running from the kelethin bank to CB. I told her I was on a CR, she said fine and stopped, only to start a few seconds later saying I had no bodies in the zone. I wasn't worried that she'd kill me cause she was a greenie, but it was irritating.  Later I sent her a tell saying that I'd been to her guild website and attacking on a cr was a big no no, to witch she replied that it was ok to attack as long as the corpse wasn't in sight.<br>
<br>
I had never heard this, and was wondering if there was a guide or anything to what is considered proper conduct for pvp on VZ. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uspyash.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Spyash</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/expert_grub/ppmaster.jpg BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/10/01 6:21:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=143.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/expert_grub/ppmaster.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: CR on VZ</span><hr size=1> Unless you are sitting on yer corpse and not looting just to be a piss ant, Then its comman curtosy not to attack the person, I would give her guild leader a little nudge and let him/her know what she is doing, Then she will wish she wasnt such a prick <p><br>Spyash Stinkyfeet<br>
